s. If he gets there, Mr Bass may even sing. Mr Krieff claims that another eight ìhuge A-list starsÅE including one supermodel, have expressed an interest in similar ventures.<br><br>As far as the rest of humanity goes, ever since the persistent Dennis Tito secured his place as the first tourist in space, he has become a rallying point for enthusiasts trying to get access to space for a broader (ie, poorer) range of customers. Initial market studies, including one by NASA, have suggested that space tourism is potentially a multi-billion-dollar market. <br><br>The single greatest barrier has always been the price. At present, the most credible efforts at cheaper transport are in the area of ìsuborbitalÅEflights. Dozens of companies are attempting to build prototype vehicles that would take tourists to the edge of space. Space Adventures has already taken 100 deposits, and some full payments, for flights on these unbuilt vehicles. They would take tourists to at least 62 miles (100 kilometres) in altitude, near the very edge of the earth's atmosphere. By comparison, passenger jets cruise at an altitude of about six miles. <br><br>Eric Anderson, Space Adventures' boss, says his company is confident that there would be ìthousandsÅEof customers willing to pay $100,000 for a 30-90 minute space experience, including five minutes of continuous weightlessness. A recent poll by Zogby International, a market-research firm, found that 19% of well-off Americans would be prepared to spend $100,000 on a short suborbital flight. The first flying prototypes, costing $10m-20m each, could be ready in as little as two years, says Mr Anderson. It would take another 18 months of testing before paying customers could get their space wings.<br><br>As for Mr Bass, time is running out to finalise a deal for the November flight to the ISS, as he needs five months of training. But if he succeeds, expect to hear more about space's youngest staróand expect other famous faces to embrace the final frontier.<br> <p><br><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace"><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nuclearspace/website/images/title/title_03.jpg"> </a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A> at: 6/13/02 6:18:14 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm24.showPrevMessage?topicID=9.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm24.showNextMessage?topicID=9.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm24.emailToFriend?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm24.threadControl?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm24.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm24.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub97.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="nucl